1.3
log
@Strip comments from install.* when installing on floppy.
Saves much needed space.
@
text
@d1 3
a3 1
#	$OpenBSD: list,v 1.2 1997/05/11 03:54:27 millert Exp $
d6 1
a6 1
COPY	disktab.preinstall			etc
d9 3
a11 6
#LINK    sbin/init                 		usr/bin/vi
COPY	dot.profile				.profile
COPY	dot.instutils				.instutils
COPY	disktab.shadow				etc/disktab.shadow

# strip comments from install scripts since we need the space
@


1.2
log
@Use the common distrib/miniroot{install.sh,install.sub}.
@
text
@d1 1
a1 1
#	$OpenBSD: list,v 1.1 1997/05/07 12:46:57 niklas Exp $
a9 2
COPY	install.md				install.md
COPY	${CURDIR}/../../miniroot/install.sh	install
d12 4
a15 1
SPECIAL sed "/^VERSION=/s/=.*/=${REV}/" < ${CURDIR}/../../miniroot/install.sub > install.sub
@


1.1
log
@*Very* rough cut at a ramdisk-kernel that fits onto a floppy.
The ecoffrdsetroot support is from millert@@openbsd.org.  Mostly copied from
the powerpc ports, thus a lot of powerpc specific stuff remains.
Needs a lot of work, hopefully done in the next few days.
@
text
@d1 1
a1 1
#	$OpenBSD: list,v 1.1 1995/07/18 04:13:12 briggs Exp $
d4 1
a4 1
COPY	disktab.preinstall		etc
d7 6
a12 7
#LINK    sbin/init                 	usr/bin/vi
COPY	dot.profile			.profile
COPY	dot.instutils			.instutils
COPY	install.sh			install
COPY	install.md			install.md
COPY	install.sub			install.sub
COPY	disktab.shadow			etc/disktab.shadow
d14 1
@
